<span id="freeTextContainer1119094872418493189"><b> <i> “How can two living entities possessing intelligence and judgement ever be tied together for a lifetime?&quot; </i></b> <br/><br/><b> This book is a Timeless Classic. This world created by R.K. Narayan, Malgudi is absolutely magical and wonderful. </b> In this, the author writes about people&apos;s day to day lives and captures everything beautifully that is all interconnected. If you haven&apos;t read this book you are missing a gem. R.K. Narayan&apos;s writing is simple and wonderful. His writing style is easy and so much relatable. Th</span>
  <span id="freeText1119094872418493189" style="display:none"><b> <i> “How can two living entities possessing intelligence and judgement ever be tied together for a lifetime?" </i></b> <br /><br /><b> This book is a Timeless Classic. This world created by R.K. Narayan, Malgudi is absolutely magical and wonderful. </b> In this, the author writes about people's day to day lives and captures everything beautifully that is all interconnected. If you haven't read this book you are missing a gem. R.K. Narayan's writing is simple and wonderful. His writing style is easy and so much relatable. This book is a collection of short stories. There is a fictional town Malgudi and the stories are about the citizens. All the characters seem real and well thought out including their struggles. <br /><br /><i> "Enchanting". Then again, "enchanting" applies to everything R. K. Narayan wrote. </i><br /><br /></span>
