<div id="review_1095946839" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1095946839" />
    <a title="Gorab" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36464297-gorab"><img alt="Gorab" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626076052p2/36464297.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1095946839?book_show_action=true">Nov 02, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gorab" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gorab" href="/user/show/36464297-gorab">Gorab</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/36464297-gorab?shelf=indian">indian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/36464297-gorab?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1095946839" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15320939231193375046">In this collection of short stories, many of the stories give a feeling of ending abruptly. But the character build up and the intrinsic details spun around EACH and EVERY story is exceptionally good. This is one of the reasons that when you feel so much acquainted with the characters, the story unfortunately has to end! </span>

          </span>
        </div>


